The paper focuses on generating video thumbnails that are dynamically related to users' search intentions with semantic correspondences to query sentences. This involves modeling both the sentence-video semantic interaction and the internal video relationships incorporated with the sentence information. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
